    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - INSTALL - MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="7">
        <title>MAINSHAFT AND COUNTERSHAFTS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the assembly from the stand (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i2">Figure 182</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i2" filename="../figg13/G13022I2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 182. Lift Assembly From Stand</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the automatic shift rail (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i3">Figure 183</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i3" filename="../figg13/G13022I3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 183. Automatic Shift Rail</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd shift fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i4">Figure 184</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i4" filename="../figg13/G13022I4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 184. 2nd - 3rd Shift Fork</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 1st-reverse shift fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i5">Figure 185</hotlnk>). Push the fork rails together.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i5" filename="../figg13/G13022I5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 185. 1st - Reverse Shift Fork</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the 4th-5th speed fork shoes are in place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i6">Figure 186</hotlnk>). A dab of light grease on the fork shoes will help them
                stay in place. Then position the assembly in the clutch housing so that the 4th-5th shift collar slides
                into the 4th-5th fork shoes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i6" filename="../figg13/G13022I6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 186. 4th - 5th Speed Fork Shoes</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply purple Loctite 515 or the equivalent to the clean housing face. Then lower the main
                case into position, making sure the forks are aligned with the shift bar support bracket in the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i7">Figure 187</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022i7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022i7" filename="../figg13/G13022I7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 187. Lower Main Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the case bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i8">Figure 188</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13022i8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022i8" filename="../figg13/G13022I8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 188. Install Case Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Tighten the bolts to 78 to 98 ft-lbs. (106 to 133 N&#183; m).</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Do not overtighten the bolts; doing so could break the unit housing and flying parts could cause
                    personal injury.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
